    "body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"installation\">\n<h1>Installation<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#installation\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p>scFates has been tested with python 3.7, it is recommended to use a <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"http://conda.pydata.org/miniconda.html\">Miniconda</a> environment.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"pypi\">\n<h2>PyPI<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#pypi\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>Currently, scFates can only be installed from <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://github.com/LouisFaure/scFates\">GitHub</a> using:</p>\n  <iframe\nsrc=\"_static/carbon.now.sh/index.html?bg=rgba%28252%2C252%2C252%2C1%29&t=seti&wt=none&l=application%2Fx-sh&ds=true&dsyoff=10spx&dsblur=27px&wc=true&wa=true&pv=25px&ph=56px&ln=false&fl=1&fm=Hack&fs=15px&lh=133%25&si=false&es=2x&wm=false&code=pip%2520install%2520git%252Bhttps%253A%252F%252Fgithub.com%252FLouisFaure%252FscFates.git\"\nframeborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height:125px; border:0; transform: scale(1); overflow:hidden;\"\nsandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\">\n</iframe></div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"r-dependencies\">\n<h2>R dependencies<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#r-dependencies\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>scFates rely on the R package <em>mgcv</em> to perform testing and fitting of the features on the peudotime\ntree. Package is installed in an R session with the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-default notranslate\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">install</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">packages</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;mgcv&#39;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"gpu-dependencies-optional\">\n<h2>GPU dependencies (optional)<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#gpu-dependencies-optional\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>If you have a nvidia GPU, scFates can leverage CUDA computations for speedups in some functions,\nthe latest version of cupy is required (at least 8.0, modify the cuda version to match yours), as well as grapheno for feature clustering:</p>\n  <iframe\nsrc=\"_static/carbon.now.sh/index.html?bg=rgba%28252%2C252%2C252%2C1%29&t=seti&wt=none&l=application%2Fx-sh&ds=true&dsyoff=10px&dsblur=27px&wc=true&wa=true&pv=25px&ph=56px&ln=false&fl=1&fm=Hack&fs=15px&lh=133%25&si=false&es=2x&wm=false&code=pip%2520install%2520cupy-cuda11%2520grapheno\"\nframeborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height:125px; border:0; transform: scale(1); overflow:hidden;\"\nsandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\">\n</iframe></div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"docker-container\">\n<h2>Docker container<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#docker-container\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>scFates can be run on a <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/louisfaure/scfates\">Docker container</a> based on Rapids container, which provide a gpu enabled environment with Jupyter Lab. Use the following command:</p>\n  <iframe\nsrc=\"_static/carbon.now.sh/index.html?bg=rgba%28252%2C252%2C252%2C1%29&t=seti&wt=none&l=application%2Fx-sh&ds=true&dsyoff=10px&dsblur=27px&wc=true&wa=true&pv=25px&ph=56px&ln=false&fl=1&fm=Hack&fs=15px&lh=133%25&si=false&es=2x&wm=false&code=docker%2520run%2520--rm%2520-it%2520--gpus%2520all%2520-p%25208888%253A8888%2520-p%25208787%253A8787%2520-p%25208786%253A8786%2520%255C%250A%2520%2520%2520%2520louisfaure%252Fscfates%253Atagname\"\nframeborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height:250px; border:0; transform: scale(1); overflow:hidden;\"\nsandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin\">\n</iframe></div>\n</div>\n",
